@startuml component-keybindings-inprogress
'' Current custom-keybinding architecture.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Custom keybindings — command registry, palette, resolver, editor, persistence

rectangle "DOM keydown" as KD RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vinary.input.keys\nKeyboardEvent -> canonical chord" as KEYS RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vinary.input.resolver\nmodal/chord state machine" as RES RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vinary.input.keymap\nactive keymap atom" as KM DATASCRIPT_TINT
rectangle "resources/keymaps/*.edn\nStandard / Vim / Emacs" as PRESETS DATASCRIPT_TINT
rectangle "vinary.input.keymaps-registry\napp-db registry helpers" as REG APPDB_TINT
rectangle "vinary.app.commands\ncommand registry" as CMD REFRAME_TINT
rectangle "vinary.ui.palette\ncommand/file palette" as PAL RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vinary.ui.keybindings-editor\nvisual editor + undo/redo" as EDIT RENDERER_TINT
rectangle "vinary.main.config\nkeybindings.edn watch/save" as CONFIG MAIN_TINT
database "~/.config/vinary-viewer/keybindings.edn" as EDN FS_TINT
rectangle "re-frame dispatch/effects" as RF REFRAME_TINT

PRESETS --> KM : compile-time defaults
CONFIG --> EDN : read/write/watch
CONFIG --> REG : vv:keymap
EDIT --> REG : edit custom sets
PAL --> CMD : choose command
KD --> KEYS
KEYS --> RES
RES --> KM : read modes/trie
RES --> CMD : resolved command id
REG --> KM : install active set
CMD --> RF : dispatch command

note bottom
  The system is available now: built-in sets, custom sets, persisted EDN,
  modal/chord resolver, command palette, visual editor, and live installation
  of the active keymap.
end note

legend right
  |= color |= concept |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| renderer UI/input |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db registry state |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| keymap data |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame command/effect layer |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| main process config service |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| user config file |
endlegend
@enduml
